<article class="plateau-playbook">
  <!-- ───── 1. Hero Section (FINAL POLISH) ───── -->
  <header class="playbook-hero">
    <div class="playbook-hero__image-wrapper">
      <img
        src="https://www.eatthis.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2023/09/weight-loss-measure-concept.jpeg"
        alt="Woman in workout gear looks down at a measuring tape, contemplating a weight loss plateau."
        width="1800" height="1000" loading="eager"
      >
    </div>
    <div class="playbook-container">
      <div class="playbook-hero__content">
        <span class="playbook-hero__kicker">The Unstuck Method</span>
        <h1 class="playbook-hero__title">5 Strategies to Break Your Fat Loss Plateau</h1>
        <hr class="playbook-hero__divider" />
        <p class="playbook-hero__subtitle">Can't seem to lose more weight? Use these five moves to fire up metabolism and watch the scale move again.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="playbook-content">
    <!-- ───── 2. Intro Section ───── -->
    <section class="playbook-section playbook-intro">
      <div class="playbook-container--narrow">
        <p>
          You’ve been disciplined. You’ve put in the work, and the results were showing. But now, the scale is stuck. That frustrating standstill is a **weight loss plateau**, and it happens to almost everyone. It’s not a sign of failure. It's a sign your body has adapted to your new lifestyle. It’s time to outsmart your metabolism and make a change.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ───── 3. Why Plateaus Happen Section ───── -->
    <section class="playbook-section">
      <div class="playbook-container">
        <h2 class="playbook-section-title">The Science of the Stall: Why You're Stuck</h2>
        <div class="playbook-grid-3">
          <div class="playbook-feature-card">
            <div class="playbook-feature-card__header">
              <h3>Metabolic Adaptation</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="playbook-feature-card__body">
              <p>As you get lighter, your body needs fewer calories to operate. Your metabolism smartly adjusts downward, meaning your old diet no longer creates a deficit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="playbook-feature-card">
            <div class="playbook-feature-card__header">
              <h3>Hormonal Shifts</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="playbook-feature-card__body">
              <p>Dieting lowers your "I'm full" hormones and raises your "I'm hungry" hormones. This biological response makes it harder to stick to your plan without a new strategy.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="playbook-feature-card">
            <div class="playbook-feature-card__header">
              <h3>Workout Efficiency</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="playbook-feature-card__body">
              <p>Your body has gotten good at your routine. It now burns fewer calories doing the same workout that used to torch fat. It's time to introduce a new challenge.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ───── 4. Strategies Section (Alternating Layout) ───── -->
    <section class="playbook-section playbook-strategies">
      <div class="playbook-container">
        <h2 class="playbook-section-title">The 5 Plateau-Shattering Strategies</h2>

        <div class="playbook-strategy">
          <div class="playbook-strategy__image"><img src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/vader-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/1670794907-steak-egg-hash-02-1e7faca3-5df7-4dfe-a6d2-6f7b55537924-1200x-1670794884.jpg" alt="A protein-rich steak and egg hash, a key meal for breaking a weight loss plateau." loading="lazy" width="600" height="600"></div>
          <div class="playbook-strategy__text">
            <span class="playbook-strategy__number">01</span>
            <h3>Up Your Protein, Adjust Your Math</h3>
            <p>Protein makes you feel fuller, longer, and burns more calories during digestion. It's your best friend in a plateau. Crucially, recalculate your daily calorie needs for your *current* weight. Your old target is likely your new maintenance level.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="playbook-strategy">
          <div class="playbook-strategy__image"><img src="https://cdn12.picryl.com/photo/2016/12/31/fitness-muscles-exercise-sports-6d9b94-1024.jpg" alt="Man performing dumbbell rows to build metabolism-boosting muscle and break a weight loss plateau." loading="lazy" width="600" height="600"></div>
          <div class="playbook-strategy__text">
            <span class="playbook-strategy__number">02</span>
            <h3>Lift Heavier to Burn More</h3>
            <p>Muscle is the engine of your metabolism. Instead of focusing only on cardio, prioritize strength training. Lifting heavier weights tells your body to build and preserve muscle, which in turn burns more calories all day long, even at rest.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="playbook-strategy">
          <div class="playbook-strategy__image"><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2024/04/26/gettyimages-1201425161_wide-7d92cc6ea15c1d67c7368b364f51230b00a7dc52.jpg?s=1400&c=100&f=jpeg" alt="People taking the stairs to increase NEAT and overcome a weight loss stall." loading="lazy" width="600" height="600"></div>
          <div class="playbook-strategy__text">
            <span class="playbook-strategy__number">03</span>
            <h3>Weaponize Your Daily Movement (NEAT)</h3>
            <p>Non-Exercise Activity Thermogenesis (NEAT) is the calories you burn from everything *but* planned exercise. Take the stairs, park farther away, stand while you work. These small, consistent efforts add up to a massive calorie burn over time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="playbook-strategy">
          <div class="playbook-strategy__image"><img src="https://images.aeonmedia.co/images/c5c24101-0b99-460c-a55c-61906cc959a7/sized-gettyimages-758285081.jpg" alt="A person getting quality sleep, essential for regulating hormones and breaking a weight loss plateau." loading="lazy" width="600" height="600"></div>
          <div class="playbook-strategy__text">
            <span class="playbook-strategy__number">04</span>
            <h3>Master Your Sleep & Stress</h3>
            <p>This is non-negotiable. Less than 7 hours of sleep can raise cortisol, the stress hormone that tells your body to store fat. It also wreaks havoc on your hunger signals. You cannot win a battle against your own biology if you are tired and stressed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="playbook-strategy">
          <div class="playbook-strategy__image"><img src="https://blog.nasm.org/hubfs/refeed-days.jpg" alt="A plate of pancakes symbolizing a strategic refeed day to reset metabolism during a weight loss plateau." loading="lazy" width="600" height="600"></div>
          <div class="playbook-strategy__text">
            <span class="playbook-strategy__number">05</span>
            <h3>Use a Strategic Refeed Day</h3>
            <p>This isn't a cheat day. It's a planned, 24-hour increase in calories, mostly from carbs. This tactic can help reset key fat-burning hormones, restock energy stores for better workouts, and provide a huge mental boost to keep you in the fight.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ───── 5. Call to Action (CTA) Section ───── -->
    <section class="playbook-section playbook-cta">
      <div class="playbook-container--narrow">
        <h2>Break Your Plateau With Certainty.</h2>
        <p>The #1 reason a weight loss plateau wins is because consistency breaks down. Life gets busy, and calorie math is hard. ICON Meals delivers the certainty you need—perfectly portioned, high-protein meals that make hitting your new macros effortless. This is how you guarantee your breakthrough.</p>
        <a href="https://iconmeals.com/collections/signature-menu" class="playbook-cta__button">Choose Your Meals</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ───── 6. Footer and Meta Info ───── -->
    <footer class="playbook-footer">
      <div class="playbook-container--narrow">
        <div class="playbook-footer__meta">
          <span>Published by the ICON Meals Team</span>
          <span>{{ "now" | date: "%B %d, %Y" }} · 5 min read</span>
        </div>
        <div class="playbook-footer__refs">
          <h4>References:</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3673773/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Metabolic adaptation to weight loss (NIH)</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/weight-loss/in-depth/weight-loss-plateau/art-20044615" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Getting past a weight-loss plateau (Mayo Clinic)</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5426284/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Role of Non-exercise Activity Thermogenesis in Human Obesity (NIH)</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>
</article>

